77 /* Tip: To avoid modifying this file each time you need to switch between these
78  devices, you can define the device in your toolchain compiler preprocessor.
79 
80  - Low-density devices are STM32F101xx, STM32F102xx and STM32F103xx microcontrollers
81  where the Flash memory density ranges between 16 and 32 Kbytes.
82  - Low-density value line devices are STM32F100xx microcontrollers where the Flash
83  memory density ranges between 16 and 32 Kbytes.
84  - Medium-density devices are STM32F101xx, STM32F102xx and STM32F103xx microcontrollers
85  where the Flash memory density ranges between 64 and 128 Kbytes.
86  - Medium-density value line devices are STM32F100xx microcontrollers where the
87  Flash memory density ranges between 64 and 128 Kbytes.
88  - High-density devices are STM32F101xx and STM32F103xx microcontrollers where
89  the Flash memory density ranges between 256 and 512 Kbytes.
90  - High-density value line devices are STM32F100xx microcontrollers where the
91  Flash memory density ranges between 256 and 512 Kbytes.
92  - XL-density devices are STM32F101xx and STM32F103xx microcontrollers where
93  the Flash memory density ranges between 512 and 1024 Kbytes.
94  - Connectivity line devices are STM32F105xx and STM32F107xx microcontrollers.
95  */
96

7896 /******************************************************************************/
7897 /* Ethernet MAC Registers bits definitions */
7898 /******************************************************************************/
7899 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Control Register register */
7900 #define ETH_MACCR_WD ((uint32_t)0x00800000) /* Watchdog disable */
7901 #define ETH_MACCR_JD ((uint32_t)0x00400000) /* Jabber disable */
7902 #define ETH_MACCR_IFG ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Inter-frame gap */
7903  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_96Bit ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 96Bit */
7904  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_88Bit ((uint32_t)0x00020000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 88Bit */
7905  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_80Bit ((uint32_t)0x00040000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 80Bit */
7906  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_72Bit ((uint32_t)0x00060000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 72Bit */
7907  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_64Bit ((uint32_t)0x00080000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 64Bit */
7908  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_56Bit ((uint32_t)0x000A0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 56Bit */
7909  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_48Bit ((uint32_t)0x000C0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 48Bit */
7910  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_40Bit ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 40Bit */
7911 #define ETH_MACCR_CSD ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* Carrier sense disable (during transmission) */
7912 #define ETH_MACCR_FES ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* Fast ethernet speed */
7913 #define ETH_MACCR_ROD ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Receive own disable */
7914 #define ETH_MACCR_LM ((uint32_t)0x00001000) /* loopback mode */
7915 #define ETH_MACCR_DM ((uint32_t)0x00000800) /* Duplex mode */
7916 #define ETH_MACCR_IPCO ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* IP Checksum offload */
7917 #define ETH_MACCR_RD ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Retry disable */
7918 #define ETH_MACCR_APCS ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Automatic Pad/CRC stripping */
7919 #define ETH_MACCR_BL ((uint32_t)0x00000060) /* Back-off limit: random integer number (r) of slot time delays before rescheduling
7920  a transmission attempt during retries after a collision: 0 =< r <2^k */
7921  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_10 ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* k = min (n, 10) */
7922  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_8 ((uint32_t)0x00000020) /* k = min (n, 8) */
7923  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_4 ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* k = min (n, 4) */
7924  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_1 ((uint32_t)0x00000060) /* k = min (n, 1) */
7925 #define ETH_MACCR_DC ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /* Defferal check */
7926 #define ETH_MACCR_TE ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* Transmitter enable */
7927 #define ETH_MACCR_RE ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* Receiver enable */
7928 
7929 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Frame Filter Register */
7930 #define ETH_MACFFR_RA ((uint32_t)0x80000000) /* Receive all */
7931 #define ETH_MACFFR_HPF ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* Hash or perfect filter */
7932 #define ETH_MACFFR_SAF ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Source address filter enable */
7933 #define ETH_MACFFR_SAIF ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /* SA inverse filtering */
7934 #define ETH_MACFFR_PCF ((uint32_t)0x000000C0) /* Pass control frames: 3 cases */
